title: Make-up free Whitney Port debuts sizeable baby bump
title_page: Make-up free Whitney Port debuts sizeable baby bump | Daily Mail Online
text:
Whitney Port went make-up free and debuted a significant baby bump while grocery shopping at Whole Foods in Los Angeles on Tuesday.
The expecting 32-year-old - who's in her second trimester - was dressed way down in a dark green sweatshirt, maroon floral pajama pants, and bright green Nike slides.
The Hills alum 'seriously can’t wait to meet' her first child, whom she felt move for the first time this week.

On Monday night, Whitney - whose morning sickness has finally subsided - revealed one of her pregnancy cravings was Swedish Fish.
'I can just cry at the drop of the hat,' Port - who boasts 2.7M followers - admitted on her YouTube vlog posted Thursday.
'Your second trimester is when you really start to see your body changing and that brings on a whole other set of emotions that you're not really prepared for. Our bodies are something that we usually have control over, and now we don't.'
